token_lists.title: Whimsy Worldz
token_lists.description:
I always loved Dr. Seuss growing up. The world always seemed like another planet with colourful truffelas, multiple legged animals, and strange, little people.

What if we could create more worlds like Dr. Seuss and like all the other geniuses of art? Imaginary trees, animals, rocks, leaves... all of nature to inspire a new place. I never knew we could create such places in real life. When I stepped into an amusement park for the first time, I realized that we could. When I saw a dream world on the big screen, I knew it was possible. When I saw all the art in museums, I thought that there are so many ideas and artists waiting to be discovered... even on the streets.

We are here now. It's an inflection point in time. Technology and creatives have formed an important relationship. We can all see each other's art and style now and share our visions - scary ones, inspiring and happy ones, beautiful fantasies, and even sad stories.

I, for one, would love to see a Tezzard dancing in a Whimsy World, or @tantan_artwork's fusion taking over Whimsy Worldz.

I am minting 300 of these worlds and gifting some to frens. It can be burned, sold, remixed, or forgotten. Just remember if you burn them, they will be known as "Lost Goodies" lol

token_lists.title: Mineral Conciousness
token_lists.description:
"[A] photograph is not only an image (as a painting is an image), an interpretation of the real; it is also a trace, something directly stenciled off the real, like a footprint or a death mask." (-S.Sontag)

This series of digital renderings and ephemera are based on 3D photogrammetry scans. Some are embellished, some are not. In some way they are all traces of the real.

token_lists.title: Macro Garden Series Vol. I
token_lists.description: Welcome to a garden that is full of multiple colors, textures and shapes, a place inspired by the smallest details of life, a collection based on focused observation, which displays a surrounding world that is almost imperceptible. Welcome to a garden that pays homage to the part of life that is always present but that we cannot see with the naked eye... a garden that makes us small in order to appreciate the greatness of our world.

token_lists.title: SIMPLY
token_lists.description: The topographic interpretation of simple rules of an cellular automata game. The initial game state is a Cyrillic writing of the word SIMPLY which after 151 turns is translated to the complex pattern. If game rules would change to reversed and the game starts from the final state then the game go reversible and go from the complex pattern to the word SIMPLE .
